        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Recommending Deaf Smith, who thinks he can induce Mexican cavalry at San Antonio to desert</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><date when="1835-10-15">Oct 15. 1835</date></p>
<p>Dear Sir</p>
<p>The <persName>bearer Erasmus Smith</persName> is well known to you&#8212;I have conversed
with him and learn that the <persName>cavalry of <placeName>San Antonio</placeName></persName> are disaffected to the
cause with which they are serving. He thinks he can render Service to us
in a certain way&#8212;Do consider if some thing cannot be done by assurances
to the disaffected through this channel.</p>

<p><persName>C. B. Stewart</persName></p>

<p><persName>Col S F Austin Comd-in [Chief] at <placeName>camp</placeName></persName></p>

<p>N B He is well known to me perhaps you may not recall him 
immediately&#8212;having travelled with him and received service and assistance at
his hands perfectly disinterested I believe that he can be trusted to any
extent his abilities and infirmity may warrant</p>

<p><persName>CBS</persName></p>


        </div1>
    </body>
